dcterms:description: The primary dataset consists of images with Chemical Structural Formulae (CSF’s) in them, some containing multiple CSF’s and other structures such as text or tables. Images were manually labeled by a domain expert into three classes: complete substances, images containing at least one Markush structure, and images that contain only Markush structures.
dcterms:title: Primary Dataset

dcterms:description: The auxiliary dataset contains complete structure images and images containing at least one Markush structure, used to further evaluate the proposed methods.
dcterms:title: Auxiliary Dataset

dcterms:description: ImageNet is a large-scale hierarchical image database used for training models in image classification tasks.
dcterms:title: ImageNet

dcterms:description: The USPTO dataset contains images of Chemical Structural Formulae (CSF’s) and images from scientific literature that do not contain CSF’s, used for pretraining models.
dcterms:title: USPTO Dataset

dcterms:creator: Elsevier
dcterms:description: Reaxys is a database that provides access to chemical information and is used in the context of chemical structure recognition.
dcterms:title: Reaxys
